content.text: I want handwash, what is the MOQ and price? I need delivery to Pakistan. My budget is 25-30 rupees per piece

content.thinking:
Let me do the budget math. 25-30 Pakistani rupees per piece. 1 USD ≈ 280 PKR. So that's about $0.09-0.11 per piece.

Handwash liquid soap typically costs $0.30-1.50/unit from China depending on size and formulation. At $0.09/unit, international sourcing can't compete — local manufacturing would be far cheaper.

I should be honest about this.

content.text:
Hey! Thanks for reaching out about handwash sourcing.

Let me be upfront — at 25-30 PKR per piece (~$0.09-0.11 USD), international sourcing from China won't work. Factory price alone starts around $0.30-0.50/unit *before* shipping and customs to Pakistan.

At your target price, local Pakistani manufacturers (Karachi/Lahore industrial zones) will be a much better fit — they can hit that range without import costs.

If your budget can stretch to 80-150 PKR/unit ($0.30-0.50), we could explore Chinese suppliers. Would that work, or is local sourcing the better path for you?
